This Presidential Memorandum, issued by President Barack Obama on January 31, 2013, delegates the functions and authority conferred upon the President by section 1306 of the Moving Ahead for Progress in the 21st Century Act (MAP-21) to the Secretary of Transportation. The Secretary is delegated the responsibility to make specified reports to Congress. The memorandum also authorizes the Secretary to notify the appropriate congressional committees and publish the memorandum in the Federal Register.